en_9338104_0	According to the duty officer of the Bandaranaike International Airport, seven flights between Chennai and Colombo have been cancelled due to heavy rain and flooding at the Chennai Airport.
en_9338104_1	Chennai is confronting its worst crisis after overnight rain that has left most of the city flooded and people wading in almost waist deep water.
en_9338104_2	Flight operations have been indefinitely suspended at the airport, trains have been cancelled and the army is helping rescue stranded people.
